Sentencas: The impact of volatile boron species on the microstructure and performance of nano-structured (Gd,Ce) O-2-infiltrated (La,Sr)MnO3 (GDC-LSM) cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells is studied for the first time.
Titulo: Impact of volatile boron species on the microstructure and performance of nano-structured (Gd,Ce)O2 infiltrated (La,Sr)MnO3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that after the heat treatment of the cathodes at 800 degrees C in air for 30 days in the presence of borosilicate glass significant grain growth and agglomeration of infiltrated GDC nanoparticles are observed.
Titulo: Impact of volatile boron species on the microstructure and performance of nano-structured (Gd,Ce)O2 infiltrated (La,Sr)MnO3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode polarization resistance of the GDC-LSM cathode after the heat treatment in the presence of glass is 3.15 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C. substantially higher than 0.17 Omega cm(2) of the cathode heat-treated in the absence of glass under identical conditions.
Titulo: Impact of volatile boron species on the microstructure and performance of nano-structured (Gd,Ce)O2 infiltrated (La,Sr)MnO3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: ICP-OES analysis shows the deposition of boron species in the cathodes after sintering in the presence of glass powder.
Titulo: Impact of volatile boron species on the microstructure and performance of nano-structured (Gd,Ce)O2 infiltrated (La,Sr)MnO3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrate the significant detrimental effect of volatile boron species on the microstructure and activity of nano-structured GDC-LSM cathode.
Titulo: Impact of volatile boron species on the microstructure and performance of nano-structured (Gd,Ce)O2 infiltrated (La,Sr)MnO3 cathodes of solid oxide fuel cells
